***ATTENTION: Please visit www.loudoun.gov/procurement to download the full solicitation.  Online responses are not accepted.  Please see the solicitation for full details on the submission process.

The intent of this Request for Proposal (RFP) is to obtain the services of qualified consultants to establish one or more fixed fee, open-ended contracts for Architectural Services in support of the County of Loudoun, Virginia (County) Capital Improvement Program and other professional architectural requirements on an “as needed” basis. The number of contracts will depend on the number and quality of the proposals received with
a maximum of five (5). Designs and project administration shall have the following characteristics:

A. Unique and functional site features for facilities that are within budget and schedule;
B. Detailed and fully coordinated architectural and engineering construction drawings and specifications;
C. Energy efficient with respect to its organization, site layout, building envelope design, and Mechanical, Electrical & Plumbing systems selection and operation,
D. Contain the necessary approvals and permits from the County of Loudoun including the Loudoun County Department of Building & Development, and all other authorities having jurisdiction;
E. Present designs and descriptions of work to Community and End User groups;
F. Superior construction administration services.

